 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Microsoft Power Platform Developer Penn State University 1,429 reviews University Park, PA Remote Full-time Penn State University 1,429 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description JOB DESCRIPTION AND POSITION REQUIREMENTS:
 Penn State IT is currently seeking a Microsoft Power Platform Developer to support the services offered by the Enterprise Solutions Digital Optimization team. The Developer will work primarily with the eSignature team to deliver enterprise level services and solutions built on the Microsoft Power Platform, including PowerApps, Power BI, SharePoint, Power Automate, Teams, custom development, and integrations with products such as Adobe Sign. Additionally, the developer will work with business partner, digital agents, and IT partners to evaluate and propose solutions; collaborate with team, product owners, business users, and technical leads to build, promote, and refine Power Platform dashboards, data visualization reports, data models, automation processes, low code application development, and general system integration. As the Power Platform expert, this role will collaborate with the team and stakeholders to define requirements, develop powerful data driven solutions, and support Power Platform training, as needed. This position is full time and can be remote. 
 
Essential Duties and Responsibilities include:
 Design and implement processes and solutions associated with a wide variety of data sets used for data/text mining, and analysis to enable informed business decisions
 Utilize connectors, leverage the AI Builder, design Power BI dashboards, build canvas apps, build Power Apps portals, and leverage Power Automate to create business process flow s
 Design end-to-end solutions that improve collaboration, productivity, and knowledge sharing
 Work with stakeholders to identify trends, aggregate data and build visually appealing reports, dashboard within Power Platform
 Develop information tools, dashboards, automation flows and queries to monitor and improve business performance
 Create solutions from initial concept to production
 Extract and compile various sources of information and large data sets from various systems to identify and analyze outliers
 Set up processes for monitoring, tracking, and trending data
 Use Agile best practice to design, develop, and maintain solutions built in enterprise applications platform s
 D evelop, d ocument , and monitor application interfaces and architecture for enterprise applications and related integrations 
 Typically requires a Bachelor's degree or higher plus 4 years of related experience, or an equivalent combination of education and experience. Additional qualifications include:
 Extensive experience in the Microsoft Power Platform – MS PowerApps, Power Automate, and Power BI required
 Strong foundational knowledge of Microso ft 365 including the Azure AD, and Azure ecosystem required
 Experience in higher education preferred
 Experience as a SharePoint Site Owner and/or Site Collection Administrator preferred
 Strong business analysis and functional understanding, including requirements gathering, creating/deploying solutions to end users
 Ability to interact with business units and coworkers in a positive and proactive manner
 Exceptional oral and written communication skills
 This position will require successful completion of standard background checks. 
